SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 186
BY SENATORS BARROW AND SELDERS
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN,
upon being named the 2026 Executive of the Year by Greater Baton Rouge Business Report.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN, upon being named the
3 2026 Executive of the Year by the Greater Baton Rouge Business Report and to
4 recognize her exceptional leadership, compassionate service, and enduring
5 contributions to medically fragile children and families throughout Louisiana.
6 WHEREAS, Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN, has been named the 2026
7 Executive of the Year by the Greater Baton Rouge Business Report; and
8 WHEREAS, she was recognized at the annual Baton Rouge Business Awards & Hall
9 of Fame gala for her mission-driven leadership and outstanding advocacy for medically
10 fragile children; and
11 WHEREAS, Renita Williams Thomas began her professional journey as a pediatric
12 nurse, and inspired by both her medical experience and her role as a mother of five, she
13 identified a critical gap in care for medically fragile children and their families in the Capital
14 Region; and
15 WHEREAS, driven by a deep commitment to serving and supporting vulnerable
16 children and their families, Renita founded "In Loving Arms Healthcare for Kids", a
17 pediatric medical daycare center dedicated to providing specialized, compassionate, and
18 skilled care in a safe, structured, and nurturing environment for children with complex
