1 medical needs; and
2 WHEREAS, through her visionary leadership as president and chief executive
3 officer, "In Loving Arms Healthcare for Kids" has become an invaluable resource to
4 countless Louisiana families, easing the immense physical, emotional, and financial burdens
5 placed upon working parents and caregivers while ensuring children receive the attentive
6 care they deserve; and
7 WHEREAS, Renita Williams Thomas' unwavering integrity, profound compassion,
8 and steadfast devotion to improving the lives of children continue to inspire colleagues,
9 caregivers, families, and the broader community; and
10 WHEREAS, she has demonstrated an abiding commitment to community service,
11 including serving on the Baton Rouge Community College Foundation Board, where she
12 actively supports educational advancement and opportunities for future generations; and
13 WHEREAS, a distinguished alumna of Southern University School of Nursing,
14 Renita Williams Thomas earned a Bachelor of Science in Nursing in 1997 and a Master of
15 Science in Nursing in 2012, exemplifying the university's enduring legacy of producing
16 leaders grounded in excellence, compassion, and service; and
17 WHEREAS, her remarkable achievement of "2026 Executive of the Year", awarded
18 by the Greater Baton Rouge Business Report, serves as a powerful testament to what
19 purposeful leadership, dedication, and vision can accomplish in service to others.
20 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
21 does hereby commend and congratulate Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN, upon being
22 named the 2026 Executive of the Year by the Greater Baton Rouge Business Report and
23 does hereby recognize her extraordinary leadership, compassionate care, and steadfast
24 commitment to medically fragile children and their families.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
26 Renita Williams Thomas, MSN, RN.
